cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "RobotDance: a Human Video to Humanoid Motion Compiler"
message: "If you use RobotDance in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Sasaki
    given-names: Ryohei
repository-code: "https://github.com/rsasaki0109/RobotDance"
url: "https://github.com/rsasaki0109/RobotDance"
abstract: >-
  RobotDance is an open-source motion compiler that converts legally available
  human videos and mocap into humanoid motion datasets, embeddings, policies,
  and robot-executable motions. It standardizes a Motion Intermediate
  Representation (RD-MIR) and provides license-safe, manifest-driven data
  pipelines, kinematic retargeting to Unitree G1/H1, MuJoCo physics-based
  feasibility checking, motion embeddings/retrieval, benchmarking, and a
  ROS2 (Jazzy) safety-gated motion runtime.
keywords:
  - humanoid
  - motion-capture
  - retargeting
  - robotics
  - ros2
  - unitree
  - human-pose
  - motion-dataset
  - text-to-motion
  - sim-to-real
  - reinforcement-learning
  - motion-generation
  - smpl
  - mujoco
version: 0.124.0
date-released: "2026-06-07"
license: Apache-2.0
